{"questionId":"9350","questionHtml":"<p>Find the volume of the sphere expressing your answer in the form <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a \\times {10^k}\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1 \\leqslant a < 10\">\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k \\in \\mathbb{Z}\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{4}{3}\\pi {\\left( {12.7} \\right)^3}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>12.7</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>8580.24&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>V</em>&nbsp;= 8.58 × 10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9350","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.1a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the volume of the sphere expressing your answer in the form a × 10 k , 1 ⩽ a < 10 and k ∈ Z .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}